  "@id": "ocp:github/cram2--pycram",
  "meta": {
    "title": "pycram",
    "description": "Cognitive Robot Abstract Machine in Python",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-09T11:15:21.662Z",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-09T11:15:21.662Z",
    "keywords": [
      "ai",
      "cognitive-architecture",
      "cognitive-robotics",
      "robotics"
    ],
    "license": "GPL-3.0"
  },
  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "- Intent-based task specification: express “what” to do using designators; the framework decides the concrete “how” at run time.\n- Late binding and adaptability: defer grounding of actions, motions, objects, and locations until execution to match the current world and robot state.\n- Composable plans: build behaviors as trees of plan nodes with clear control-flow constructs (sequential, parallel, retry, repeat, monitor).\n- Introspection and observability: plans track node status, timing, and context for debugging, visualization, and monitoring.\n- ORM-backed persistence: automatically capture plans, actions, spatial data, and outcomes in a relational schema for analysis and reproducibility.\n- Reusable across robots: separate intent from embodiment so the same high-level logic can target different platforms.\n- Motion building blocks: ready-to-use motion designators (e.g., TCP and gripper control) compose into higher-level actions like pick-up and transport.\n- World model integration: operate over bodies, links, transforms, and semantic annotations; reason about objects and places, not only coordinates.\n- Simulation-first workflow: run end-to-end plans in simulation for rapid iteration, with optional visualization.\n- Clear validation points: action and motion steps can declare pre/post conditions to verify success (e.g., object grasped).\n- Data-driven improvement: stored execution traces support benchmarking, failure analysis, and experiment tracking.\n- Modular and extensible: define custom designators, actions, and plan patterns while leveraging the common orchestration and logging.\n- Tested examples and demos: runnable scenarios (e.g., PR2 pick-and-place) illustrate typical workflows and best practices.",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
